{"batchcomplete": "", "query": {"pages": {"1069944": {"pageid": 1069944, "ns": 0, "title": "Tales from the Crypt (film)", "contentmodel": "wikitext", "pagelanguage": "en", "pagelanguagehtmlcode": "en", "pagelanguagedir": "ltr", "touched": "2026-02-20T22:08:47Z", "lastrevid": 1339302331, "length": 23579, "fullurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tales_from_the_Crypt_(film)", "editurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Tales_from_the_Crypt_(film)&action=edit", "canonicalurl": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tales_from_the_Crypt_(film)", "pageprops": {"defaultsort": "Tales From The Crypt (Film)", "displaytitle": "<i>Tales from the Crypt</i> (film)", "page_image": "Tales_from_the_crypt_film_poster.jpg", "wikibase-shortdesc": "1972 British film by Freddie Francis", "wikibase_item": "Q1615432"}, "description": "1972 British film by Freddie Francis", "descriptionsource": "local", "extract": "Tales from the Crypt is a 1972 British horror film directed by Freddie Francis. It is an anthology film consisting of five separate segments, based on short stories from the EC Comics series Tales from the Crypt by Al Feldstein, Johnny Craig, and Bill Gaines. The film was produced by Amicus Productions and filmed at Shepperton Studios in Surrey, England.\nIn the film, five strangers (Joan Collins, Ian Hendry, Robin Phillips, Richard Greene and Nigel Patrick) in a crypt encounter the mysterious Crypt Keeper (Ralph Richardson), who makes each person in turn foresee the manner of their death. It is one of several Amicus horror anthologies produced during the 1970s.", "categories": [{"ns": 14, "title": "Category:1972 British films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:1972 English-language films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:1972 films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:1972 horror films"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:All Wikipedia articles written in British English"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Category:All articles containing potentially dated statements"}, {"ns": 14, "title": "Catego